<br>
Honestly, I think the rollbacks are not necessary, considering that the cash was legit drops (albeit somewhat insane) and not people duping plat or some such nonsense.  I certainly don't remember anyone getting rolled back from the &quot;Shadowhaven Cheese Incident&quot; and there were people making quite a bit of plat from that, including all those folks selling dairy spoons at 100p each.<br>
<br>
Of course with all that extra cash floating around, basic economics says that prices would've seen massive inflation (as what everyone saw over the past weekend with stupid flowing slime boots selling for 150k), but it still seems like Sony should've just fixed the bug rather than do rollbacks and ultimately punish innocent vendors (and yes, many folks who sold tons of high end gear ended up getting rolled back and their items returned).<br>
